## intuition

Let $X_1,\ldots,X_n ~ F_{\theta}(\cdot)$ be independent and identically distributed random_variables. The statistic $T(X_1,\ldots,X_n)$ is sufficient for $\Theta$, $\iff$ The joint probability_density_function (or [[probability_mass_function]]) The joint distribution can be factorised into $f(x_1,\ldots,x_n) = g(t,\theta)h(X_1,..,X_n)$
## rigour
We say an estimator is sufficient when it does not depend on theta
